result.execSummary:
The defendant Alex P. Morales was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of THC, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Case called @ 3:48 p.m. Defendant Alex P. Morales in court with attorney Ben Szilagyi.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  The parties stipulate to Judge Dutcher presiding over the plea/sentencing hearing as there is an agreement. The Court will preside over the matter without the written consent from Judge Bult under the general 6th District authority. Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: Ct 1 - NC.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC.  No statement by DE. Court orders: 45 days WCJ - Huber, GT, 2 days CFTS - Sentence to commence by no later than 3/15/2016, costs w/ 60 DTP or PP, DNA Sample and Surcharge ordered by the Court.  Defendant advised of right to expunge DNA record through the Department of Justice. Appeal rights given. Bond previously posted to be applied. The Court orders counsel to obtain written authorization from Judge Bult releasing the case back to Judge Dutcher.

records.descr: Application for specific judicial assign approved

records.addlTxt: The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing/ingesting any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.   No operation of any motor vehicles without a valid driver's license.

Case Called @ 2:02 PM: Defendant Alex P. Morales in court with attorney Ben Szilagyi.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.    NGP received and entered.  SPD states that Def intends to exercise his right to Substitution of Judge.  Written Substitution to be filed.  DA argues as to bond.  No objection to bond requested.
